00:07:37,560 --> 00:07:38,960
should do.

230
00:07:38,960 --> 00:07:39,840
Obviously,

231
00:07:39,840 --> 00:07:41,520
culture includes many concepts.

232
00:07:41,520 --> 00:07:43,120
It includes ideas,

233
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:44,680
beliefs,

234
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:46,840
behaviors,

235
00:07:46,840 --> 00:07:48,520
and traditions.

236
00:07:48,520 --> 00:07:49,120
These things

237
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:51,720
are all part of our culture.

238
00:07:51,720 --> 00:07:53,120
How can we

239
00:07:53,120 --> 00:07:55,080
conduct a research

240
00:07:55,080 --> 00:07:56,720
on such a complex issue?

241
00:07:56,720 --> 00:07:58,600
Fortunately,

242
00:07:58,600 --> 00:08:01,360
some research has shown us

243
00:08:01,360 --> 00:08:02,840
that different cultures

244
00:08:02,840 --> 00:08:05,160
have certain ways

245
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:08,040
to distinguish different cultural characteristics.

246
00:08:08,640 --> 00:08:11,840
We call this

247
00:08:11,840 --> 00:08:14,600
a pre-existing

248
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:16,120
theoretical framework.

249
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:17,800
As researchers,

250
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:18,720
if we are curious

251
00:08:18,720 --> 00:08:19,840
about the cultural factors

252
00:08:19,840 --> 00:08:21,000
that can explain

253
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:22,240
why parents

254
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:24,600
suffer from parental burnout,

255
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:26,080
we may be able to

256
00:08:26,080 --> 00:08:27,720
use the theory structure

