00:08:27,720 --> 00:08:30,720
of cultural differences

258
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:31,880
in the past

259
00:08:31,880 --> 00:08:33,760
to explain

260
00:08:33,760 --> 00:08:37,560
whether these cultural factors

261
00:08:37,560 --> 00:08:38,680
can predict

262
00:08:38,680 --> 00:08:39,640
parental burnout.

263
00:08:39,640 --> 00:08:40,640
This is a very intuitive

264
00:08:40,640 --> 00:08:42,800
and simple research.

265
00:08:42,800 --> 00:08:43,760
On the other hand,

266
00:08:43,760 --> 00:08:45,280
we can imagine

267
00:08:45,280 --> 00:08:46,120
that parental burnout

268
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:51,040
is a very specific phenomenon.

269
00:08:51,040 --> 00:08:53,240
It occurs in

270
00:08:53,240 --> 00:08:55,000
our parental environment.

271
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:57,240
We may doubt

272
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:58,440
that if we use

273
00:08:58,440 --> 00:09:01,280
the general theoretical framework

274
00:09:01,280 --> 00:09:02,160
to explain

275
00:09:02,160 --> 00:09:03,680
parental burnout,

276
00:09:03,680 --> 00:09:05,160
we may ignore

277
00:09:05,160 --> 00:09:06,520
the important

278
00:09:06,520 --> 00:09:08,680
cultural concept of parental burnout.

279
00:09:08,680 --> 00:09:10,240
It may be that

280
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:10,840
we can predict

281
00:09:10,840 --> 00:09:11,520
that parental burnout

282
00:09:11,520 --> 00:09:12,640
is a very important concept

283
00:09:12,640 --> 00:09:13,920
and we ignore it.

284
00:09:13,920 --> 00:09:14,920
In order to make up

285
00:09:14,920 --> 00:09:16,200
for this phenomenon,

286
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:16,960
in addition to using

287
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:18,360
a very simple

288
00:09:18,360 --> 00:09:19,880
or straightforward

289
00:09:19,880 --> 00:09:22,160
research trend like TopDown,

290
00:09:22,160 --> 00:09:23,120
